.TH "xs_udp_write_space" 9 "xs_udp_write_space" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
xs_udp_write_space \- callback invoked when socket buffer space becomes available
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "void" xs_udp_write_space
.BI "(struct sock *sk "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "sk" 12
socket whose state has changed
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
Called when more output buffer space is available for this socket.
We try not to wake our writers until they can make "significant"
progress, otherwise we'll waste resources thrashing kernel_sendmsg
with a bunch of small requests.
